<title>USA: HBO say to post charge after acquisition.</title>
<headline>HBO say to post charge after acquisition.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA, Ga. 1997-06-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>HBO &amp; Co said on Thursday that it had completed the previously announced acquisition of Enterprise Systems Inc and that it would take a one-time charge for acquisition-related expenses.</p>
<p>HBOC said ESI shareholders received 0.4579 of a share of its common stock with a value of $30.00 per ESI share.</p>
<p>At closing, roughly 3.8 million HBOC shares were issued for the about 8.3 million outstanding ESI shares, the healthcare management software company said in a statement.</p>
<p>HBOC added that the transaction will be accounted for as a pooling of interests, and that it will take a one-time charge for acquisition-related expenses.</p>
<p>ESI offers resource management products for healthcare organizations.</p>
